        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 5:59PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 25
miles north of West Glacier, or 46 miles north of Evergreen, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Goat Haunt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
